{{Top|leg}}
{{Quote|Daala reclaimed a leadership position with the new warlords of the Deep Core. Successors to Harrsk, Delvardus, and the others now held power within the Deep Core kingdoms, and while warlords such as Foga Brill and Moff Tethys lacked military muscle, they made up for it in base cruelty.|[[Voren Na'al/Legends|Voren Na'al]]|<ref name="TNEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref>}}
The '''replacement warlords''' were an alliance within the [[Deep Core/Legends|Deep Core]] of [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Warlord/Legends|warlords]] who succeeded the thirteen Imperial warlords that had been executed by [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Natasi Daala|Daala]] in [[12 ABY/Legends|12 ABY]]. They eventually formed the [[Second Imperium]].

==History==
===Successors===
{{Quote|Still trying to impose order, Daala united the squabbling factions to make preparations for a uniﬁed strike against the New Republic.|Voren Na'al|<ref name="TNEC" />}}
The replacement warlords were located at the [[Deep Core/Legends|Deep Core]] when [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Natasi Daala]] [[Death/Legends|executed]] the thirteen most powerful [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] warlords in [[12 ABY/Legends|12 ABY]] at [[Tsoss Beacon/Legends|Tsoss Beacon]], leading to the [[Imperial Reunification]] and the creation of the [[Imperial Remnant]]. Few of the replacements possessed the strategic talents or resources commanded by those killed by Daala, but compensated with base cruelty and repression.<ref name="TNEC" />

The replacement warlords included [[Moff/Legends|Moffs]] [[Foga Brill/Legends|Foga Brill]], [[Jmanuel Tethys]],<ref name="TNEC" /> [[Bliss Shargael]],<ref name="DoaE1">{{SW|url=news/the-imperial-warlords-despoilers-of-an-empire-part-1|series=The Imperial Warlords: Despoilers of an Empire|text=Part 1|nolive=1}}</ref> and [[Grand Moff/Legends|Grand Moff]] [[Cinzero Gann]].<ref name="DoaE3">{{SW|url=news/the-imperial-warlords-despoilers-of-an-empire-part-3|series=The Imperial Warlords: Despoilers of an Empire|text=Part 3|nolive=1}}</ref> [[Brakiss]] became a neutral power broker among them following his involvement in the [[Almanian Uprising]].<ref name="TNEGtC">''[[The New Essential Guide to Characters]]''</ref><ref name="TNEC" />

Following her [[Battle of Nam Chorios|defeat]] of Moff [[Tol Getelles|Getelles']] forces in [[13 ABY/Legends|13 ABY]], Daala returned to the Deep Core and became the leader of a coalition of these warlords, eventually planning strikes into [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[Realspace/Legends|space]]. After the [[Battle of N'zoth|end]] of the [[Black Fleet Crisis]] in [[17 ABY/Legends|17 ABY]], [[Camp Pa'aal Squadron|surviving Imperial forces]] of [[Sixth Negative Regions|Black Sword Command]] escaped to [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine's]] throneworld of [[Byss/Legends|Byss]]. Upon learning of the [[Planet/Legends|planet's]] [[Destruction of Byss|destruction]] [[Standard year/Legends|years]] earlier, some of them defected to the New Republic while others joined the Imperial Remnant and other Imperial forces. Four [[Victory-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Victory''-class Star Destroyers]] joined the Imperial Deep Core warlords.<ref name="TNEC" />

In 17 ABY, the [[Council of Moffs/Legends|Council of Moffs]] of the Imperial Remnant secretly contacted Admiral Daala to launch a joint [[Imperial Skirmishes|campaign]] against the New Republic.<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> However, the squabbling warlords could not provide a united front even with Daala's leadership, and the New Republic's [[New Republic Fourth Fleet|Fourth Fleet]], led by [[General/Legends|General]] [[Garm Bel Iblis/Legends|Garm Bel Iblis]], launched a crippling series of assaults on their perimeter. In the [[Battle of Columus (Galactic Civil War)|Battle of Columus]], Bel Iblis defeated Daala, forcing her flagship to escape into [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]]; it remained unaccounted for.<ref name="TNEC" /> Defeated, the Imperial Remnant was forced to negotiate a [[Pellaeon–Gavrisom Treaty|declaration of peace]] with the New Republic [[19 ABY/Legends|two years later]].<ref name="TEA" /> However, the replacement warlords themselves remained and they rejected these accords. They severed allegiance to the official Imperial Remnant and later re-organized themselves as the [[Second Imperium]].<ref name="TNEGtC" />

===The Second Imperium===
{{Main|Second Imperium}}
{{Quote|Aren't there still some Imperial strongholds in the Core Systems?''"<br />"''Sure are.|[[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]] and [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]]|<ref name="Young Jedi Knights: The Lost Ones">''[[Young Jedi Knights: The Lost Ones]]''</ref>}}
In [[18 ABY/Legends|18 ABY]], the leader of the [[Constitutional Protectorate of Prakith]] Moff Brill was assassinated by [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] and his [[Lando's Commandos|commandos]] on his [[Fortress world/Legends|fortress world]] of [[Prakith/Legends|Prakith]].<ref name="DoaE3" />

The Second Imperium was eventually [[Second Imperium Crisis|defeated]] by the New Republic and the [[New Jedi Order]] in [[23 ABY/Legends|23 ABY]].<ref name="TNEC" /> By the time of the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], the New Republic had finally [[Attacks on Imperial holdouts|cleared]] their enemies out of the Deep Core.<ref name="DW">''[[The New Jedi Order: Destiny's Way]]''</ref>

